text.section:
Subject to the hearing provisions of Title 2 of this article, the Commissioner may deny a registration to a pharmacy benefits manager applicant or refuse to renew, suspend, or revoke the registration of a pharmacy benefits manager if the pharmacy benefits manager, or an officer, director, or employee of the pharmacy benefits manager:
makes a material misstatement or misrepresentation in an application for registration;
fraudulently or deceptively obtains or attempts to obtain a registration;
in connection with the administration of pharmacy benefits management services, commits fraud or engages in illegal or dishonest activities; or
violates any provision of this part or a regulation adopted under this part.
